Xavier Hamori - Luxembourg, MFS Investment Management | about.meXavier HamoriConducting and Compliance Officer in LuxembourgRead my blogI am currently acting as Conducting and Compliance Officer for MFS Investment Management Company (Lux) S.à r.l., a Luxembourg-based UCITS management company authorized by the CSSF under chapter 15 of the Law of 17 December 2010 relating to undertakings for collective investment.In my Compliance Officer role, I oversee the compliance function of the management company and its branches, which include among others the implementation of the compliance program and the related controls and procedures. I am also in charge of the quality and efficiency of the processes and procedures, including those relating to ethical and conduct matters, portfolio compliance and distribution compliance.In this role, I report to the Conducting Persons and the Board of Managers and Directors of the Management Company and the Funds. I usually report monthly to the Conducting Officers, and quarterly to the Board. Due to the nature of the function, I am involved in a number of internal committees.I also act as Money Laundering Compliance Officer. In this role, I am in charge of preparing, developing and maintaining the AML Program and to report accordingly to the Conducting Persons, the Board and the relevant authorities (the Luxembourg Financial Intelligence Unit “CRF” and the CSSF where applicable).The Management Company manages two Luxembourg-based UCITS, one SICAV and one FCP, for a total amount of around € 35 billions of assets. MFS is an asset manager based in Boston with a worldwide presence and a history of 90 years.#luxembourg#reviseurdentreprises#expert-comptable#compliance#isqc1WorkMFS Investment Management


